Description: Ibanez S7320 7 string electric guitar for sale, with ZR tremolo. Everything works fine and it plays great with nice thin wizard neck, set up with nice action, in excellent shape was barely played, only problems are a couple hairline scratches and small dings, and some tarnished screws on the tremolo, see pics. The trem is set up works well and stays in tune, the screw wheel makes it really easy to set up with new strings, also includes ZPS2 stabilizer which I took out for easier tremolo, but it's easy to just pop it back in. Comes with Gator guitar slinger bag, new Sinister Strings 7 string set, original 700 dollar receipt for the guitar, and other stuff pictured. Thanks for looking The S7320 is a seven string S series solid body electric guitar model introduced by Ibanez in 2007. It was the first seven string S series model since the 2000 S7420. It was initially made in Korea, but production was shifted to Indonesia starting in 2008.The S7320 features a sculpted body bolted to a maple neck with a 22-fret fretboard with pearloid dot position markers. Components include a pair of Ibanez Axis humbucking pickupsand a ZR double locking tremolo bridge with a removable ZPS2 tuning stabilizer.In 2009, a white finished S7320 was offered in some countries.
